
# My Learning Journal

This is my personal **Learning Journal** website. I created it to document my journey learning frontend development and to showcase my projects. I will be updating it as time goes on.

## Features

- **Responsive Design**: Mobile-first with CSS Grid, Flexbox, and media queries.
- **Homepage**:
  - Hero section with a featured post
  - Recent posts grid (first 6 shown, "View more" button reveals the rest)
- **Article Page**: Full post with related image and recent posts
- **About Page**: My bio, photo, and recent posts
- **Contact Page**: Email, portfolio, GitHub, and Netlify links
- **Navigation**: Responsive navbar with hamburger menu on mobile
- **Interactive Elements**: Hover effects for navigation and buttons, "View more" functionality

## Skills Practiced

- HTML5 & semantic structure
- CSS3 (Flexbox, Grid, responsive units)
- JavaScript (DOM manipulation, event handling)
- Mobile-first design
- Accessibility and user experience

## How to Use

1. Clone this repository
2. Open `index.html` in a browser
3. Replace images and text with your own learning content